File: Bafana Bafana beat Mali 2-1 on Sunday. JOHANNESBURG - The SABC and SAFA have announced a four-year agreement to broadcast six Bafana Bafana matches, five Banyana Banyana matches and a number of lower division games as well. WATCH: Bafana Bafana visit Nelson Mandela Children’s Hospital This brings to an end the standoff between SAFA and the SABC which saw National team matches disappear off the screens. SAFA President, Dr Danny Jordaan is welcoming the agreement. WATCH: SAFA committed to pay bonuses to Banyana Banyana The Nelson Mandela Challenge between Bafana Bafana and Mali will be broadcast on Sunday at 3pm.